metadata.name: Broken Window #16
metadata.description:
hello again fxHash 1.0!

I'm back. Very very inspired by the latest work of one of the best artists, jjjjjohn, with his work entitled Broken Mirror. Of course I come up with a solution for those who can't afford the works of the greatest jjjjjohn. This work was created with layered png and templates from PureSpider.

I give the reserve list to those who hold Bottle and Apples. In addition, I also give 25% of the 25% royalty of this work to the minter. Reserve slot will disappear after 2 cycles. So public can have it too.

If this piece doesn't sell out, that's okay. Maybe because my name is not jjjjjohn.

metadata.name: A collage of collages #588
metadata.description:
Lots of eyes, lots of mouths, lots of other features. Don't know how else to describe how else it goes.

Almost all the eyes are from GAN projects, some are from CC0 searching. Everything is either GAN or CC0, no copyrighted materials used here. Specific feature or otherwise. 

The number of potentials for this is SUPER hight, I think it's 10*10*9*10*12*10*9 combinations

Hope you enjoy!

metadata.name: Hash Effects #121
metadata.description:
Hash Effects is an introspective graphical performance that discovers its own abstract origins and morphs it into concrete forms.

The origins of these artworks lie within the transaction hash that results from minting a unique edition of the artwork. Each graphical trait in the artwork is controlled by this origin, so in essence the transaction hash is responsible for the entire artwork.

While most generative artworks hide their transaction hash in abstraction, Hash Effects shows it front and center. Each unique artwork celebrates its own transaction hash as a graphical element that morphs into various shapes over different animation scenes.
